      "issue": "Kafka offset committed before event processing — payment events will be silently lost on consumer crash",
      "reason": "This is a data-loss bug in a financial system. The offset must be committed AFTER successful processing or AFTER successful DLQ publish. This is not a nice-to-have — it is a correctness requirement for payment event handling. Shipping this pattern means any crash, OOM kill, or pod eviction during processing permanently loses payment data with no trace.",
